data.value:
A CHIP-8 emulator written in C# - just for the fun of it.
What is CHIP-8: CHIP-8 is an interpreted programming language, developed by Joseph Weisbecker. It was initially used on the COSMAC VIP and Telmac 1800 8-bit microcomputers in the mid-1970s. CHIP-8 programs are run on a CHIP-8 virtual machine. It was made to allow video games to be more easily programmed for said computers. - source: en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CHIP-8
